Yeah, SJW-Cancel Culture-Digging on 10 year old jokes-stuff is horrible, but honestly, you'd think someone killed his dog or something. Freedom of speech goes both ways: no-one can (or shouldn't be able to, let's not go down that rabbit hole) prevent you from saying ANYTHING. You can say whatever you want. BUT. It's also freedom of speech for people to get upset about what you said. They can and should express themselves over it, if you say it in a public forum. It's not like I can go to a children's hospital's cancer ward and go yell "I fucking love that your children have leukemia, you fucking deserve this you fat cunts" and not expect to get some people riled up. 

If you respect your own freedom of speech, you have to express other peoples too. You can't have your cake and eat it too, that's what freedom of speech is about. You say stuff, you own up to that stuff. Even if it is a joke, you have to acknowledge the fact that not all people are going either get the joke or think it's funny.

2:15:10 I spent about 2 years not doing shit. I used to take all the callous every week for about a year and a half and I worked 2 jobs and between the 2 it was 7 days a week for a long time. Then I quit the second job, quit taking everyone's weeks for callouts and got real fuckin lazy for 2 years. I sit so much at my job driving from place to place and we are at a house for an avg of 2 mins or so. Then after sitting all day I'd get home and not want to do shit even more. For 2 years this went on and on and on. After 2 years, my legs started to hurt from such a lack of use. I finally had enough and started walking laps around the shop at work during lunch. Then after a few days I'd do 10 squats per lap and it's just went on and on from there. I haven't eaten lunch at work in over a year. I can't say I was doing brutal leg workouts, but for someone who was always skinny, but never had leg muscles, every day when I was done that shit hurt. After about 6 months, I discovered Goggins and my motivation turned to a bit of drive. I started around my birthday last year on 8/13/18. Around the time I found Goggins, I also looked at myself in the mirror and was juuuust starting to gain some weight. I weighed 197. I had never been over 180 before. I could see myself starting to get fat. So, I added in upper body workouts at home. It was a slow process and wasn't super consistent in the beginning but I never stopped my leg stuff at work. I only missed 2 days in over a year now. Any day I go to work I make myself do it so if there is a holiday, vacation day or sick day, I give myself that day off only. Well, after a year of legs and 6 months of upper body, I'm down to 167 lbs and looking not too bad. Don't get me wrong, I have a long fucking way to go, but that motivation that turned to a little bit of drive is full on drive now. This is the person I am now. Starting on my birthday this year, I just turned 38 and I finally got my ass up that morning at 4 am and started running. I hate running but I am making myself do it. 4 am every day I go to work so usually 5 days a week. Then as of a few weeks ago, I started getting to work around 6 am and doing a morning leg workout and still doing my lunch routine. I actually have leg muscles for the first time in my life. My thighs look like I'm wearing football pads on the outside! My stomach is almost completely flat, I have abs again and I'm in the best shape I've ever been in. Every day I'm doing something. I do upper body at home, but since I hated leg workouts the most, that is what I put most of my focus into and it's finally paying off. Found a way to get my inner leg and calf muscles and they are starting to show too. My body hurts like a mother fucker all the time, but it's so much nicer knowing it hurts from working my ass off than from sitting on my ass getting fatter by the day. I was gonna hurt one way or the other so why not make it hurt by being productive?? I even found a stationary bike at work to add in as well. Anyone can do this. Just don't start off with some ridiculous workout or you may want to give up early. Just slowly build. Problem is it takes time. A LOT of time. You just have to jeep going and it will pay off. I have cut my 2 1/2 packs of cigarettes a day down to no more than 26 in a day and many days being at 20 or less, down from 50 a day. Small steps but they add up. The hardest part of this entire journey I've been on by far, was the first step. Once I took that first step it's been downhill from there as far as it being hard to do. It's a great feeling to know when I start the work day at 7am I'm quite probably the only one who has put in any work on themself and gotta be the only one to put THAT much work in. It's an unbelievable feeling. I used to have trouble sleeping really badly. Now, when I lay down in a few minutes or less, I'm out cold and sleep through the whole night because I'm wearing myself out. ANYONE CAN DO THIS! Yes even you!! Floods have spread the waste to rivers and lakes, polluting them to the point where they cannot support marine or avian life -- if a fish lives through it, you don't dare eat it! Misinformation on Andrew Yang starts at 1:07:12. Here is the issue

1. Andrew Yang argued we need to stop subsidizing pollution. We need to tax items that pollute based on their true pollution cost - the cost to undo/mitigate that pollution 

2. An example he mentioned was beef and how beef has a huge CO2 footprint compared to other foods. [my insertion: 500 cal of beef is equivalent to driving 13 miles, while 500 cal of chicken is equivalent to driving only 3.5 miles]. Andrew Yang is arguing for a tax that works just like the tax on gasoline we are all comfortable with. The more miles we drive, the more gas tax we have to pay, to fix the roads we used and the environment we polluted.

3. It's not about cow farts/methane [that is a very small part of the equation]. The big thing is that chicken and even pigs are more efficient at converting their feed into meat. So if you want beef over chicken, you have to cut down more trees, to clear the land to grow the cow food. Those forests store CO2. Lots of it.

4. Yang has never mentioned anything about animal rights, nor anything about the health benefits of plant-based diets. In fact, we've seen Andrew Yang eat Turkey and Chicken on TV, so he definitely isn't vegetarian. Your rant about veganism was so off-topic. It obviously has nothing to do with Yang.

replies.commentText: I use to work in the repair department of a major electronics manufacturer alongside predominantly mainland Chinese  repair techs, and they would tell me that the difficult part of learning English wasn't the grammar or the syntax, it was the sheer number of words to learn that was daunting. Even though there are literally thousands of Chinese characters in the written language, the spoken languages and dialects of that ancient and vast land are each only composed of maybe 10,000 or so total words. English and German (the first and second richest languages in terms of total number of words in the vocabulary) on the other hand, contain many times that number of total words, a fact which I suspect is unknown to Mark Normand, yet strongly supports his theory in terms of empirical data. Also, he's not saying that people outside of the English speaking world aren't funny, he's merely suggesting that the richness of the English language (along with a unique cultural history of stand-up comedy which was born in the modern Western Civilization) enhances the ability of any person with a natural sense of humor to convey it more effectively to an audience of mostly total strangers. Nuance plus knowledge goes a long way my dude.

To give a an old/new for some perspective on Michael Jackson people dont realize what kind of upbringing Michael Jackson had, and how that affected him as he grew up and had not a sexual attraction to children, but he actually over empathized and cherished the innocence of kids.

Michael Jackson and his brothers were brought up under a strict Jehovah's Witness religion that NEVER CELEBRATED BIRTHDAYS,  HOLIDAYS, HALLOWEEN,  THANKSGIVING  CHRISTMAS, ETC.... 
Throughout MJs childhood his Father kept Michael away from other kids. He was home schooled and never had other kids to play with whatsoever. 
Michael was beaten by his dad if he didn't practice and do the right thing to make the band sound right.
Even when Micheal became famous at age 6,7,8,9 he NEVER GOT TO PLAY WITH KIDS or Exchange gifts for Christmas or got gifts on birthdays.
And while he was doing Ed Sullivan show at Christmas time he'd see other kids from a distance having fun and opening gifts and doing things normal kids got to do and he never got to share in those experiences. 

When he finally broke out from under his fathers strict religious upbringing  Michael's mind was like a kids mind that never grew up

This is why he built Neverland...and invited children who could never afford to go to Disneyland to come to his property that he dedicated to the enjoyment of chdren.

Of course this was setting MJ up to be accused by the parents of child abuse. 
Child abuse would never cross Michael's mind because he suffered as a kid .
People looked at Michaelas a weird pedophile,  when in fact Michael was a protector of kids, and allowed them to enjoy themselves without worrying about expenses, etc.

Michael cherished kids and their innocence because he lost his kid identity as he grew up. He loved seeing kids enjoy themselves on rides, and he would live through their innocent experiences and seeing through their eyes all the things he missed out on as he was being abused by his dad.

I dont think Michael Jackson ever made a sexual advance towards any children . He knew what it felt like to lose his innocence,  and he cherished that and would never break a kids trust like his was while he grew ip.

That's my rant...and I'm not a black person trying to defend him. I  am just relaying my truth to you for review
